I've seen all sorts of interesting wild animals while on motorcycle rides. Eagles, bears, elk, bison, white wolves, penguins, zebra, monkeys, and more...

But never in my life would I have imagined I'd need to dodge giant spiders crossing the road!

This is a Western Desert Tarantula, otherwise known as an Arizona Blonde. It's a young male on a mating quest, and seeing one cross the highway is fairly rare, even if you're in the right place at the right time. We saw probably 8-10 of these guys over the course of 2k miles, traversing the highways of Nevada and California.

They're harmless to humans and only bite if seriously threatened. They don't mind being handled, but we couldn't get them to crawl on our hand. Our gloves probably smell like fuel, oil, and dust from all over the world. I imagine it's a little overwhelming for a creature that rarely leaves it's burrow. We helped him cross the road safely.

#motorcycle #tarantula #spooder #nevada #arizona #roadrunner #roadrunnermagazine #hondagoldwing #lasvegas #girlswhoride #wildlife #getoutside #explore #adventure #desert

My restless soul is dreaming of spending more time in this place. 

The more I travel, the more I struggle with the monotony of daily life. The grind. Hours in front of a computer, tied to a desk, paying bills. Hustling 24/7. Caught up in the race that is life and success. 

All I truly want is to spend time in nature. Lay on beds of moss and ferns surrounded by trees and fog. Watch water droplets form on petals of flowers and blades of grass. Listen to the animals. Talk to the earth. 

Is that so much to ask for?

We rode 1000 miles through the Nevada desert in search of whales. We found several varieties, but to find out which kinds you'll just have to read the full story...

_____

A recap of what these photos mean to me...

Riding through Death Valley. We were only delayed by 30 minutes to take a detour to Badwater Basin to check out the temporary playa lake. Then by another 30 minutes while I stood in line waiting for change for the penny smushing machine. It was worth it.

Riding into the sun rise was a gift. We finished with an hour to spare. I was SO glad to see the sun again. 34 degrees for 500mi was tough. 🥶

The lake that formed in Death Valley won't last long. These playa lakes are incredibly rare, and the result of a massive rain just as the cooler temps swept across the valley.

I purchased the most expensive fuel of my life, and it was only 91 octane. 

Death valley is the hottest and driest place in North America and Badwater Basin is 282ft below sea level. Such a cool spot to visit even though  I had to run a mile to get the photo of the lake.

______

You can find the full story "Whale Hunting in the Desert & the 1000 Mile Cheesburger" (our first of the Inconvenient Iron Butt series) in the Jan/Feb '24 issue of @roadrunnermag 

Trust me, this is a good one. You don't wanna miss it!
